# CODEOWNERS — convention reference (no real owners assigned yet).
#
# This file is intentionally a placeholder for a fresh project: there are no committed
# code owners. It documents the *convention* so that, as the team grows, ownership can
# be added by uncommenting and editing the rules below.
#
# How CODEOWNERS works (recap):
#   - Each line is a glob followed by one or more @users / @org/teams.
#   - LATER MATCHING rules override earlier ones (last match wins).
#   - GitHub auto-requests review from listed owners on any PR touching matching files.
#   - Combine with branch protection ("Require review from Code Owners") to enforce it.
#
# Conventions we will follow once owners exist:
#   - Default owner = the smallest team that can credibly review anything in the repo.
#   - Security-sensitive paths get an explicit security-reviewer team in addition.
#   - CI / build infrastructure is owned by whoever maintains the toolchain.
#   - Docs can have a separate, lower-friction owner (often the same default team).
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Example rules — UNCOMMENT AND REPLACE @org/team placeholders when owners exist.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Default owner for everything in the repo (catch-all; should be the LEAST specific rule).
# *                              @your-org/maintainers

# CI, build, repo plumbing. Changes here can affect every PR's signal, so review carefully.
# /.github/                      @your-org/platform
# /scripts/                      @your-org/platform

# Security-relevant code: auth, crypto, session handling, headers, input validation.
# Add the security team in addition to the default reviewer.
# /src/auth/                     @your-org/maintainers @your-org/security
# /src/crypto/                   @your-org/maintainers @your-org/security
# SECURITY.md                    @your-org/security

# Docs can move with a lighter touch.
# /docs/                         @your-org/docs
# README.md                      @your-org/docs

# Package manifests must be reviewed by maintainers — Dependabot bumps included.
# package.json                   @your-org/maintainers
# package-lock.json              @your-org/maintainers
